[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dementia care home in Williamstown to create 50 jobs

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new Â£1m dementia care home in Rhondda Cynon Taff will create 50 jobs, the operator has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Welsh-owned Silvercrest Group plans to open the 33-bed home in Williamstown, near Tonypandy, in the autumn.
Chief executive Dr Bikram Choudhary said they were recruiting nurses, carers and administration staff.
He said the home would "provide a much needed service in RCT and Taff Ely".
